By Our Correspondent A member of the House of Representatives from Plateau State, Hon. Haruna Ibrahim Maitala, is dead. Maitala, also known as Turakin Jere, died in a road accident along Bade-Gitata road Friday evening while on his way to Jos, the Plateau State capital. According to a Facebook post, Maitala died alongside his son, driver and security aide, who were all traveling with him. Until his death, he represented Bassa/Jos North federal constituency of Plateau State in the House of Representatives. His death comes barely a month after another member of the Green Chamber, Hon. Yuguda Killa from Jigawa State, passed on.